<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key: E major (4 sharps). Hymn uses I-IV-V with modal D#/Eb regions.
- "Eb" chord annotations treated as B major (⑤) — the D# is the leading tone of E.
- "Ebm" chord annotations also treated as B (⑤) — D#m in E major context is the VII diminished, substituted with dominant B.
- Opening bars 1-4: Clean "334" open voicings (E2 B2 E3 G#3) for spacious E major texture.
- Bars 4, 21, 26: EΔ7 (Emaj7) used at peak phrases — D# in bass adds leading-tone tension.
- Bar 9/17: Full harmonic rhythm (1 chord/beat) — F#m→C#m descending thirds very effective.
- Bar 11: Quartal "44" voicing (E2 A2 D#3 G#3) for modern color on repeated G# melody.
- Bar 20: RH arpeggio F#5→D#5→B4 over open B bass — descending arpeggio contrasts with rising melody.
- Bar 27: Final dominant B "33" with strong bass before final E.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 9 RH descending D#5→C#5→B4 mirrors LH bass rising B→F#→C# — contrary motion.
- Common tone B shared between E and B (I and V) — always in bass layer.
- Bar 13 RH descending E5→C#5→A4 arpeggio provides natural linear motion over static melody.
- Bar 15 B→E transition: LH bass steps B2→E2, only a 4th — minimal motion.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 0-6: Sparse opening (3-note LH), half-note harp values — airy, hymn-like texture.
- Bars 7-14: Middle phrase — quarter-note LH motion in bars 9/13, fuller 4-note chords.
- Bars 15-21: Climax section — EΔ7 voicings, RH arpeggios, B7 → E resolution.
- Bars 22-28: Final repeat of opening — slightly fuller (EΔ7 in bar 26), converging to quiet final E.
-->
